A few / A little vs Few / Little

We use few / little when something has a negative meaning - we don't have as much as we want, or as we expected.

She has few friends.

I have little money.

We use a few / a little when something is more positive - we may have enough or more than we expected.

He has a little soup.

I have a few dollars left.

Reminder : few or a few are used with plural countable nouns; 
little or a little are used with singular or uncountable nouns.

